<subsection xml:id="subsec-line-graphs">
        <title>Line graphs of data</title>
        <p>
            Line graph of data is a visual representation of data where individual data points are connected by straight lines, showing how a variable changes over time or across a continuous scale, typically with the horizontal axis representing time and the vertical axis representing the measured values.
        </p>
        <p>
            It is used to identify trends and patterns in data over a period of time.
        </p>
        <activity>
            <p>
                <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Work in groups}}</m>
            </p>
            <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Consider the table shown on the amount of recorded rainfall in a place for a period of six months.
                    </p>
                    <table>
                        <title>Amount of Rainfall for a period of six months</title>
                        <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium" >
                            <row halign="left" header="yes">
                                <cell>Month</cell>
                                <cell>Jan.</cell>
                                <cell>Feb.</cell>
                                <cell>March.</cell>
                                <cell>April.</cell>
                                <cell>May.</cell>
                                <cell>June.</cell>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <cell>Amount of Rainfall(mm)</cell>
                                <cell>50</cell>
                                <cell>70</cell>
                                <cell>80</cell>
                                <cell>150</cell>
                                <cell>140</cell>
                                <cell>110</cell>
                            </row>
                        </tabular>
                    </table>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Represent the information on a line graph.
                    </p>
                </li>
                 <li>
                    <p>
                        Share and discuss with other groups.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
            </p>
        </activity>
        <p>
            <m>{\color{black} \textbf{Key Takeaway}}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                    In line graphs, points are connected with straight lines to represent changes in values over a period of time.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        </p>
        <example>
          <statement>
            <p>
                The table shown represents the sale of motorcycles by a company from the month of June to December 2021
            </p>
            <table>
                <title></title>
                <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                    <row halign="left" header="yes">
                        <cell>Month</cell>
                        <cell>June</cell>
                        <cell>July</cell>
                        <cell>Aug.</cell>
                        <cell>Sept.</cell>
                        <cell>Oct.</cell>
                        <cell>Nov</cell>
                        <cell>Dec.</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>No. of motocycles</cell>
                        <cell>10</cell>
                        <cell>40</cell>
                        <cell>30</cell>
                        <cell>20</cell>
                        <cell>30</cell>
                        <cell>40</cell>
                        <cell>50</cell>
                    </row>
                </tabular>
            </table>
            <p>
                Draw a line graph to represent the information
            </p>
          </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    Scale 1 cm represents 10 motorcycles.
                </p>
                <image width="50%">
                <latex-image>
                    \begin{tikzpicture}
                        \begin{axis}[
                           xlabel={Month},
                           ylabel={Number of Motocycles},
                           xtick=data,
                           xticklabels={June, July, Aug, Sept, Oct, Nov, Dec},
                           ymin=0, ymax=60,
                           xmin=1, xmax=8,
                           grid=both,
                           ytick={0, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60}, 
                           grid=both,
                           mark options={solid}
                        ]

                        \addplot[
                           color=blue,
                           mark=square*,
                           thick
                        ] coordinates {
                           (1,10)
                           (2,40)
                           (3,30)
                           (4,20)
                           (5,30)
                           (6,40)
                           (7,50)
                        };
                        \end{axis}
                    \end{tikzpicture}
                </latex-image>
                </image>
            </solution>
        </example>
